so we will call you when it is over.
I see.
Okay.

Yeah, yeah!

I see.

Azuki?

Hey!
When we were together in the hospital, I wanted to stop time.
My, it is pretty romantic.
Sorry I read it.
Miura.
TEN or Future Watch...
It must be tough to choose, huh?
Huh?
Choose?
Huh?
Am I wrong?
Did I say something I should not have?
No...
Miura.
I am glad that Business Boy Kenichi seems to be doing well.
Oh, yeah.
The first chapter took 6th.
The second was 8th.

You were right to put in jokes.
Putting in jokes was the right decision?

Is it true that they are more stable in the surveys than serious stories?
Here...
Here, too!
Hello?

I am sorry about earlier.
The lecture is over, so I am free to talk now.
Uh, yeah.
Um... sorry, I am busy right now.
Can you wait until I call you?
So he said.

because neither of our one-shots did well?
Past survey results?
I want to look at as much data as I can.

so you cannot view those on a computer.
The voting slips are supposed to be somewhere in the editing department, but...
I will look for them!
The storyboard you faxed me was pretty good,
so I wanted to meet with you as soon as possible.
Thank you.

I read it with admiration.

Only...

I would like you to write it from Shouchirou's point of view.
Okay.
This may be rude, but you are pretty, so you must have a lot of experience with relationships, correct?
Oh, if you interpret this as sexual harassment, please tell me right away.

A lot?
I do not wish to go into detail, but I have had my fair share.
Oh, sorry.

No one in particular.
I have several friends, though.
Do you understand men's feelings from your previous relationships?
Well...
This is important.

I do not know whether I should give you my viewpoint as a man,
or if you should just rely on your own experiences.
I am fine.
I will write it on my own.
I will be counting on you for the revision, then.
From the guy's point of view.
I understand.
Thanks for your work today.
Should I have answered him honestly instead of trying to show off?
Things like men's feelings... and love...
For someone like me, who is only had unrequited love and never dated...
Because I love you!
No!
That is not...

Getting serialized is wonderful!
I am happy just doing any job related to manga.
I see, I see!
I understand completely.
Sometimes, I think being an assistant is easier, too.

Wondering?
Why?
I will be 30 soon.
I need to start thinking about marriage.
Marriage, huh?
Kato, do you have a b-boyfriend?
No way.
I am a manga otaku.
Really?
I would have thought you would be popular.
Should I offer myself as a candidate?
You are so silly, Nakai.
Aoki Kou?
Yes.
I said it at the restaurant, did not I?
Aoki, I like you!
Oh yeah, you slipped that out during the confusion.
So this woman is a bit...
I am not good with older women.
Did not you say you wanted someone to take care of you?
I want to be taken care of by younger girls!

Anime?
All I said was that it would be nice, right?
But the offers coming in...
I said it would be nice if they were.
Was that bait, too?
Well, yeah.
I guess I cannot take all these with me.
For now, these documents will be enough.
No, this too...
I should take this, too.

It is been a week already.
Yeah.

I do not know.
I am sorry it took so long to get back to you.
It is not finished yet, but here is the storyboard for Future Watch.
Can you take a look?
No.
I am thinking of submitting TEN to the next serialization meeting.
This is not what we agreed on!
Future Watch had the higher ranking!
Right!
TEN was 10th, and Future Watch was 9th.
First, look at these data charts.
Hmm, I see.
Out of the past serializations which started out as one-shots that ranked within the top ten,
the gag manga stayed in place and had the potential to change.
That is right!
It is hard to shake the rating of a manga with lots of jokes.
Even if it does drop, it is easier to get it back up than with a serious manga.
But the key here is that the average age of TEN's readers is 13.6.
For Future Watch, it is 18.7.
Looking at past data, it is clear that a younger demographic leads to longevity.
Dragging old data into this is meaningless.
Not as many kids read it now.
That is exactly why it is important to appeal to kids!
For a one-shot within the top ten,
it is easier to get a serialization with a gag manga, and it will be longer-lived!
Um, we will not be satisfied with just a long-lived serialization.
We want a big hit!
All I hear you saying is that we will scrape by with a long-lasting serialization that will not be very popular.
Please let us do Future Watch!
Putting aside the data, Takagi's better suited to that!
But according to this data, manga with jokes have the advantage.
Data is important and can be trusted.
Sorry.
I like my facts.
It is true that Kinnikuman actually started out as a gag manga.
REBORN!, too.

it is possible to start a second phase with battles.
Yeah, maybe we should go with TEN.
Shujin...
Of course, only if it is okay with you, Saiko.

You just have to make it so that they do not really die.
Then the setting would lose its meaning!
And I do not know if Shujin's jokes will be popular or not.
No, Takagi's jokes are what one would call classic,
and I think they will be popular with kids.
Kids like old men's humor!
Well, if the level of humor in the TEN one-shot is fine, it might work out.
That is fine!
I do not think it will become a hit!
Takagi's okay with it!
The data supports it, too!
Why are you so against it?
Because Takagi is not suited for it, like I have said a million times!
Takagi himself is saying that he will be fine doing it!
But only if I am fine with it, too!
Were not you listening?!

Something is wrong there!

or Takagi can get someone else to draw for him!

I have got no choice.

you have to get someone else to draw!
Saiko, let us go.
We cannot deal with this guy.
Uh, Shujin!
Hey, wait up!
I am so pissed.

I cannot forgive him!
Shujin.
Yeah?

Huh?!

If you want to do it...

Not happening!

Yeah.

Saiko, Hattori, Eiji.

I do not know what to do.

I do not want to see him at all.
Damn.
I am panicking.
Let us go home and think about it tomorrow.
Okay.

No.
Thanks for your time...
Hey.

Jack?

Nakai?
No.

Akino Aiko?

Thank you.

Why manga?
Why?
Because I love manga.

I would be happy to.
Hattori!

What happened?
Tell me.

Yes.

Yes.

I do not think we should go that far.

Yeah.

I am sorry!
